==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scyllaea
<hw>Scyl*lae"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Scylla</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of oceanic
nudibranchiate mollusks having the small branched gills situated on the
upper side of four fleshy lateral lobes, and on the median caudal
crest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In color and form these mollusks closely imitate the
fronds of sargassum and other floating seaweeds among which they
live.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scyllarian</ent>⟦br⟧
